bestowed
by many partial parents, upon the vain
parade of forming the manners of a child,
and burthening the mind wiht the
necessity
of
the douceurs and the graces, would it not
often be happier for both, to take a finall
share
of thought to kindle
one
spark
of grace
in the heart?
HAPPY the parents, who have
bestowed
upon their children
such
an education, as
will enable them, by a principle of
mediocrity
,
to govern them without extorting
obedience
,
and to reclaim them without
exercising
severity
.
Farewel!
