The Court of Vice
.
An APOLOGUE.
VICE on a
solemn
night of
state
,
In all her pomp of terrour
sate
,
Her voice in deep, tremendous tone,
Thus
issu
'd from her ebon throne:
`This night at our infernal court,
`Let all our
ministers
refort;
`Who
most
annoys the human race,
`At our right hand
shall
take his place,
`Rais'd on a throneadvanc'd in fame
`Ye CRIMES now vindicate your claim.'
Eager for
praise
, the hideous
host
,
All
spake
,
aspiring
to the
post
.
PRIDE
said
, to gain his private ends,
He
sacrific
