By caufing envy and diffentions.
INTEMP'RANCE loud, demands the place,
He'd long deceiv'd the human race;
None could
such
right as he maintain,
Disease
and death were in his train.
THEFT next appears to claim the
station
,
E'er
constant
in his dark vocation;
He thought the place might well repay,
The
crime
who labeur'd night and day.
FRAUD own'd (tho' loth to
speak
